I '''Usain St. Leo Bolt''', [[Order of Jamaica|OJ]], [[Order of Distinction|C.D.]] ({{IPAc-en|icon|ˈ|juː|s|eɪ|n}};<ref>Ellington, Barbara (2008-08-31). [http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080831/lead/lead2.html He is a happy person, says Usain's mother]. ''[[Jamaica Gleaner]]''. Retrieved on 2009-08-05.</ref> a mibait anyang 21 Agosto 1986), metung yang [[Jamaica]]n a talapulaying tuturing da reng keraklan a pekamabilis a tau king kasalesayan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tampabay.com/sports/olympics/gary-shelton-at-the-games-usain-bolt-leaves-no-doubt-he-is-the-fastest-man/1244402|title=Usain Bolt leaves no doubt he is the fastest person ever|accessdate=2012-08-10|date=05 August 2012|work=St. Petersburg Times |first=Gary|last=Shelton}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2012/08/07/spo01.asp|title=Lightning Bolt strikes London 2012|accessdate=2012-08-10|date=06 August 2012|work=Daily News|first=Dinesh|last=Weerawansa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/usain-bolt-olympics-gold-2012-8|title=Usain Bolt Striking His Famous Pose After Winning Gold At The Olympics|accessdate=2012-08-10|date=05 August 2012|work=Business Insider|first=Dinesh|last=Weerawansa}}</ref> 
Ya ing mumunang lalaking tinalan kareng titulu king [[100 metres|100&nbsp;metres]] ampong [[200 metres|200&nbsp;metres]] [[List of world records in athletics|a record ning yatu]] manibat anyang inumpisan da ing [[pamanyukad ning oras a laganas a otomatiku]] (''fully automatic time measurements'').

Kayabe la reng kayabe na king koponan, gewa ne murin ing record a pangyatu king [[4 × 100 metres relay|4×100&nbsp;metres relay]]. Ya ing makalukluk a kampeon king Olympics kareng atlung pangapalyaring (''event'') deti, ing mumunang taung sumambut anam a [[gintung medalya]] king [[Sprint (pamamulayi)|sprinting]], ampong mekatalimang kampeon king yatu (''five-time World champion''). Ya ing mumunang taung mika "double double" kapamilatan ning pamanyambut na king 100&nbsp;m and 200&nbsp;m titles kareng mitutuking Olympics (2008 ampong 2012),<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/olympics/la-sp-oly-track-20120810,0,3872429.story|title=Usain  Bolt gets a legendary double-double in Olympic sprints|accessdate=2012-08-10|date=10 August 2012|work=Los Angeles Times|first=Helene|last=Elliott}}</ref> at ligpusan ne ini king mumunang "double triple" (kayabe ya ing 4x100m relays).<ref>{{cite web|title=London 2012 Day 15: Bolt does the double – triple|url=http://www.euronews.com/2012/08/12/london-2012-day-15-bolt-does-the-double-triple/|accessdate=12 August 2012}}</ref> 

Ing kayang lamang a mekabalbal record anyang 2009 king [[Men's 100 metres world record progression|100&nbsp;m]], manibat 9.69 (manibat king sadya nang record a pangyatu) anggang 9.58, ing pekamatas manibat anyang ning [[pamanyukad oras a lubusang otomatiku]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/08/20/AR2009082004135.html|title=Jamaican Sprinters Such as Usain Bolt Quickly Reshape Nation's Identity|accessdate=2009-08-23|date=21 August 2009|work=The Washington Post |first=Paul|last=Farhi}}</ref> 

Uling kareng kayang tagumpe king sprinting, meyaus yang "Lightning Bolt",<ref name=Focus>{{Cite news|author=Lawrence, Hubert; Samuels, Garfield |title=Focus on Jamaica – Usain Bolt |url=http://www.iaaf.org/news/athletes/newsid=36356.html |work=Focus on Athletes |publisher=[[International Association of Athletics Federations]] |date=20 August 2007 |accessdate=2008-06-01 }}</ref> and awards including the [[IAAF World Athlete of the Year]], [[Track & Field Athlete of the Year]], ampong [[Laureus World Sports Award for Sportsman of the Year|Laureus Sportsman of the Year]] (makatadwa).
 
Ya ing pekamatas panakitan a atleta king track and field.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/kurtbadenhausen/2012/08/04/how-usain-bolt-earns-20-million-a-year/|title=How Usain Bolt Earns $20 Million A Year|accessdate=2012-08-10|date=04 August 2012|work=Forbes|first=Kurt|last=Badenhausen}}</ref>
Inaus de muring ''world’s most marketable athlete'' <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sportspromedia.com/sportspro_blog/usain_bolt_is_the_worlds_most_marketable_athlete/|title=Usain Bolt is the world’s most marketable athlete|accessdate=2012-08-12|date=17 May 2011|work=SportsPro |first=Tom|last=Love}}</ref>
ampong ''the greatest athlete ever''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://futures.tradingcharts.com/news/futures/Jim_Souhan__Usain_Bolt_greatest_athlete_who_ever_lived_183537161.html|title=Usain Bolt greatest athlete who ever lived|accessdate=2012-08-12|date=9 August 2012|work=Futures and Commodity Market News|first=Jim|last=Souhan}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://grg51.typepad.com/steroid_nation/2009/08/greatest-athlete-of-all-time-usain-bolt-sets-world-record-time-of-1058-seconds-100m-in-berlin.html|title='Greatest athlete of all time' -- Usain Bolt -- sets world record time of an 9.58 second 100M in Berlin|accessdate=2012-08-12|date=17 August 2009|work=SteroidNation}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/athletics/6043869/World-Athletics-Championships-To-Usain-Bolt-all-things-are-now-possible.html|title=World Athletics Championships: To Usain Bolt, all things are now possible|accessdate=2012-08-12|date=12 August 2012|work=The Telegraph}}</ref>

